commit.message:
Don't bind user-reserved keys

See `(info "(elisp) Key Binding Conventions")`, particularly the
following tip:

> Function keys <F5> through <F9> without modifier keys are also
> reserved for users to define.

Merge pull request #9 from rothmichaels/master

Only insert boilerplate AS when in actionscript-mode.

Only insert boilerplate AS when in actionscript-mode.

The previous implementation relied on a `filename` variable being set;
this could be a source of bugs if called from an unexpected location.

Calling `insert-flash-boilerplate` from `find-file-not-found-hooks` was
too global and was causing this function to be called from unexpected
locations. Now it is called as part of the `actionscript-mode-hook` on
empty buffers.
